import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import { Alert } from './Alert'

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"alert"}}>{`Alert`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"properties"}}>{`Properties`}</MDXTag>
<PropsTable of={Alert} />
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"basic-usage"}}>{`Basic usage`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __position={1} __code={`<Alert>Some message</Alert>`} __scope={{props,Alert}}>
  <Alert>Some message</Alert>
</Playground>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"using-different-kinds"}}>{`Using different kinds`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __position={2} __code={`<Alert kind="info">Some message</Alert>
<Alert kind="positive">Some message</Alert>
<Alert kind="negative">Some message</Alert>
<Alert kind="warning">Some message</Alert>`} __scope={{props,Alert}}>
  <Alert kind="info">Some message</Alert>
  <Alert kind="positive">Some message</Alert>
  <Alert kind="negative">Some message</Alert>
  <Alert kind="warning">Some message</Alert>
</Playground>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"use-with-children-as-a-function"}}>{`Use with children as a function`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __position={3} __code={`{() => {
  const message = \'Hello world\'
  return <Alert>{message}</Alert>
}}`} __scope={{props,Alert}}>
  {() => {
    const message = 'Hello world'
return (
  <Alert>{message}</Alert>
)
  }}
</Playground></MDXTag>
